					<h1><a href="http://borgidacpas.com/2010/12/how-the-new-tax-law-may-impact-you/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to How the New Tax Law May Impact You">How the New Tax Law May Impact You</a></h1>
					<!--<div class="author">Author: <a href="http://borgidacpas.com/author/karen-tedford/" title="Posts by Karen Tedford">Karen Tedford</a></div>-->
					
				</div>
				<div class="entry">
					<p>On December 17, 2010, President Obama signed the tax bill into law after months of negotiations, and to our benefit, this law will be in effect for the next two years.&nbsp; Enactment of this tax law confirms that individuals at all income levels won&rsquo;t face an automatic hike in taxes beginning in January 2011.&nbsp; There are several areas to talk about and some key points to consider now that the holiday season is over and tax season is upon us. <a href="http://borgidacpas.com/2010/12/how-the-new-tax-law-may-impact-you/#more-1609" class="more-link">more&#8230;</a></p>
